results.description: Melanerpes cactorum (Orbigny, 1840) is a species of woodpecker. It's commonly known as the white-fronted woodpecker and it's native to central South America, Its range includes southeastern Peru, Bolivia, Uruguay, northern Argentina, Paraguay and southeastern Brazil. These species roam the trees, pecking at the bark, looking for their food. They use the pilothouse (tail) feathers for additional support. They can be supported both on vertical trunks and branches, as well as under horizontal branches and it is not usual to observe them on the ground.
